description: Testing rules — automatically applied when editing test files
globs: ["**/TESTS/**", "**/TESTS/"]
alwaysApply: false
---

You are working on tests. Read `rules/testing-guidelines.md` before proceeding.

Key constraints:
- Test reports must be saved to `TEST_REPORTS/<YYYY-MM-DD-HH-MM-SS>-<MODULE>/test-report.md` at the project root. Never inside `TESTS/`.
- Module-level tests: `modules/<MODULE>/TESTS/`
- Sub-module-level tests: `modules/<MODULE>/<SUB_MODULE>/TESTS/`
- Python: use `pytest` or `unittest`. JavaScript/TypeScript: use `jest`, `vitest`, or `cypress` (E2E).
- Tests must be independent and not rely on execution order.
